Privacy Policy for Evntos

Effective Date: 11/1/24

Evntos (“we,” “us,” or “our”) values your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect the information you provide when using the Evntos app. By using Evntos, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect

When you use Evntos, we may collect the following types of information:

a. Personal Information
	•	Name
	•	Email address
	•	Phone number (optional)
	•	Profile picture (optional)
	•	Event-related details such as RSVP status

b. Location Information
	•	Geolocation data for event check-in and check-out purposes (only with your consent).

c. Device Information
	•	Device type, operating system, and app usage data to improve app performance.

d. Event Information
	•	Event details such as event name, time, date, and participant lists.

2. How We Use Your Information

We use your information for the following purposes:
	•	To create, manage, and share events.
	•	To enable event check-in and check-out functionality.
	•	To send event notifications and updates.
	•	To improve app functionality and provide personalized experiences.
	•	To comply with legal obligations.

3. How We Share Your Information

We do not sell or rent your personal information. However, we may share your data in the following situations:

a. With Event Organizers
	•	Event organizers may have access to your check-in and check-out status.

b. With Service Providers
	•	We may share data with third-party service providers who assist us in delivering and maintaining the app.

c. For Legal Compliance
	•	We may disclose your information to comply with applicable laws or respond to lawful requests.

4. Data Retention

We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. Once the data is no longer needed, we securely delete or anonymize it.

5. Your Rights and Choices

You have the following rights regarding your information:
	•	Access: You can request access to the personal data we hold about you.
	•	Correction: You can request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete information.
	•	Deletion: You can request that we delete your personal data, subject to legal obligations.
	•	Opt-out: You can opt out of receiving promotional communications.

To exercise these rights, contact us at [Insert Contact Email].

6. Security Measures

We use industry-standard security measures to protect your data, including encryption, secure servers, and access controls. However, no system can guarantee absolute security, and we encourage you to safeguard your account credentials.

7. Children’s Privacy

Evntos is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware of such data, we will delete it.

8. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will notify you through the app or via email. Continued use of Evntos after such updates constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.

9. Contact Us

If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
Email: alfredojr@alfredoamezcua.com


By using Evntos, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to its terms.
